 -- DistroForge maintainers <maintainers@distroforge.invalid>  Tue, 02 Jun 2026 20:25:00 +0200

distroforge (0.3.4-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix the maintainer chroot terminal, which echoed nothing and reacted to
    nothing. When the chroot shell exits it closes the slave end of the PTY,
    and a PTY master then signals end-of-stream by raising EIO instead of
    returning EOF. The poll loop only handled the would-block case, so once
    the shell had exited every poll tick raised through read() and the
    session's own cleanup never ran: the status stayed on "Running" and the
    /dev /dev/pts /proc /sys /run bind mounts leaked. read() now treats EIO as
    end-of-stream, so the loop drains the child's final output, reports its
    exit code, and releases the runtime mounts instead of leaking them.
  * Add a Start button at the leading edge of the header bar that returns to
    the project start page from any other surface, following the GNOME HIG
    convention of a back/home affordance at the start of the header. It is the
    always-visible, recognition-over-recall counterpart to the keyboard
    "Open tool…" command palette, shown on every surface except the start
    page itself.

 -- DistroForge maintainers <maintainers@distroforge.invalid>  Mon, 01 Jun 2026 19:09:32 +0200

distroforge (0.3.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Keep the GUI fully responsive under the wider Adwaita Sans metrics: every
    dynamic single-line label now elides to an ellipsis with the full text in
    a tooltip, and the dashboard stat tiles carry a width floor, so a value
    such as "Ubuntu 26.04 skeleton" can no longer overflow or clip inside its
    panel at any window width. A responsive test sweeps every page across a
    range of widths and fails on any label drawn wider than its own frame.
  * Give DistroForge an autonomous, GNOME-native colour identity. A new
    palette module transcribes the GNOME Human Interface Guidelines palette
    verbatim and maps a single semantic set on top of it -- primary and
    secondary accent plus success, warning, error and info -- all sourced from
    those named colours. The accent is GNOME Blue, replacing the former
    per-desktop accent (which defaulted to the Ubuntu orange) and the ad-hoc
    status hues, so the product reads as its own GNOME-native tool rather than
    a Canonical / Vanilla-framework derivative. The GUI still follows the
    host's light/dark scheme; only the surfaces and signals now come from one
    palette.

 -- DistroForge maintainers <maintainers@distroforge.invalid>  Mon, 01 Jun 2026 00:49:03 +0200

distroforge (0.3.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Render the Adwaita symbolic icons that 0.3.1 introduced: the toolbar and
    action buttons now resolve every glyph through the same Adwaita symbolic
    theme as the build-phase list, instead of Qt's built-in widget pixmaps,
    so the whole window draws from one GNOME-native icon source.
  * Recommend qt6-svg-plugins: the Adwaita symbolic icons are SVG, and this
    package supplies the Qt SVG icon engine that draws them. Without it Qt
    cannot render the theme glyphs and silently falls back to its built-in
    set, which is why the new icons were invisible. As a Recommends the GUI
    still degrades gracefully when it is absent.

